I too loved the flash game Gemcraft when I was younger but I was confused why it was $10 on steam, surely it couldn't be worth it but I was intrigued enough to follow my curiosity and here's how I would compare the the free version to this one;

The free version is like an attractive woman walking past you, "she's pretty" you might think but it doesn't really change your day or anything.

This game is like banging a cheerleader and a supermodel for hours on end, they don't want you to stop and you don't want to do anything else.

17416743.review:
- extremely simple and intuitive mechanics (including keyboard shortcuts for everything);
- grind, although obviously present, is far from boring, thanks to the "only XP above previous best count" - makes one try to replay levels on harder settings instead of repeating the same thing over and over again.
- skill mechanics, allowing to tailor player's abilities to what one wants to achieve;
- story. There's quite little of it, yet it's quite captivating.

All in all, definitely worth it, even at full price.
